WEBVTT

00:00.792 --> 00:01.882
[gunshot fires]

00:01.919 --> 00:02.879
- I’ve spent some
time with you,

00:02.920 --> 00:04.880
I’ve spent some
time with Chucky,

00:04.922 --> 00:07.722
and I gotta say
I like you better.

00:07.758 --> 00:09.088
[screams]

00:09.134 --> 00:10.554
- I thought you quit.

00:10.594 --> 00:12.224
You seem weird.

00:12.262 --> 00:15.022
- Holy homemade bomb, batgirl.

00:15.057 --> 00:16.387
- Why are you doing this?

00:16.433 --> 00:19.443
- There were 72
of me on that truck.

00:19.478 --> 00:21.648
- This is for Kyle.
[engine roars]

00:21.688 --> 00:23.148
[crash]

00:23.190 --> 00:25.110
- Exactly how many
of you are left?

00:25.150 --> 00:27.900
- Enough to make this
worth the sacrifice.

00:27.945 --> 00:28.905
[suspenseful music]

00:28.946 --> 00:30.106
[screams]

00:30.155 --> 00:32.275
- [giggles]
- Gary!

00:32.324 --> 00:34.414
- These kids are responsible
for Gary’s death.

00:34.451 --> 00:37.201
- [screams]
- It was a tragic accident.

00:37.246 --> 00:39.456
I’ve done some work
with troubled youth

00:39.498 --> 00:42.128
at the School of
the Incarnate Lord.

00:42.167 --> 00:43.627
- He blew himself up.

00:43.669 --> 00:45.299
He’s never done anything
like that before.

00:45.337 --> 00:47.507
No matter what,
he’s gonna come for us again.

00:47.548 --> 00:49.378
- Guys, why does this place
look so familiar?

00:49.424 --> 00:51.264
- Charles Lee Ray lived
here when he was our age.

00:51.301 --> 00:53.891
- Welcome to Incarnate Lord.

00:53.929 --> 00:55.389
Do you know why you’re here?

00:55.430 --> 00:56.810
- ’Cause God hates us?

00:56.848 --> 00:58.638
- He wants you to seek
forgiveness

00:58.684 --> 01:00.944
and to find your way
back to him.

01:00.978 --> 01:03.098
- [evil chuckling]

01:03.146 --> 01:04.516
[ominous music]

01:04.565 --> 01:06.825
[crow cawing]

01:06.858 --> 01:13.658
♪ ♪

01:13.699 --> 01:16.159
- [yawns]
Mm.

01:16.201 --> 01:23.291
♪ ♪

01:28.171 --> 01:30.971
[grunts, sighs]

01:31.008 --> 01:33.888
[chilling music]

01:33.927 --> 01:35.967
[whimpers]

01:36.013 --> 01:40.853
♪ ♪

01:40.892 --> 01:42.852
No.

01:42.894 --> 01:43.984
No, no.

01:44.021 --> 01:46.521
[whimpering]

01:48.734 --> 01:51.744
[screams]

01:51.778 --> 01:57.658
♪ ♪

01:57.701 --> 02:00.451
[crows caw]

02:05.042 --> 02:06.002
[elevator dings]

02:06.043 --> 02:09.003
[suspenseful music]

02:09.046 --> 02:10.506
♪ ♪

02:10.547 --> 02:13.297
- [humming]

02:13.342 --> 02:20.432
♪ ♪

02:26.438 --> 02:28.938
Good morning, sweet face!

02:28.982 --> 02:31.362
Rise and shine!

02:31.401 --> 02:32.991
- What was that screaming?

02:33.028 --> 02:35.278
- Oh, I’m sorry, Nica.

02:35.322 --> 02:37.742
I didn’t mean to disturb you.

02:37.783 --> 02:39.743
I was just--it was--

02:39.785 --> 02:42.165
[grunting]

02:43.080 --> 02:46.540
I--I had a bad dream.

02:46.583 --> 02:49.753
- Well, that was probably
your fucking conscience.

02:49.795 --> 02:51.215
- Breakfast!

02:52.381 --> 02:55.761
I don’t want to argue, Nica,

02:55.801 --> 02:58.931
not when I’m so happy.

02:58.970 --> 03:00.600
Are you happy?

03:00.639 --> 03:04.769
Are you as happy
as you make me?

03:04.810 --> 03:07.020
- Take a wild guess.

03:07.062 --> 03:08.562
- Uh-oh.

03:08.605 --> 03:13.065
Somebody woke up on the wrong
side of bed this morning.

03:13.110 --> 03:14.570
[chuckles]

03:15.654 --> 03:19.284
Come on now.
What’s the matter?

03:19.324 --> 03:22.454
- You chopped off my arms
and legs, you lunatic.

03:22.494 --> 03:24.704
- We’ve been
through this before.

03:24.746 --> 03:28.166
I cut off
Chucky’s arms and legs,

03:28.208 --> 03:32.458
so he can never come
between us ever again.

03:32.504 --> 03:36.474
- You kept me prisoner
in this house for a year.

03:36.508 --> 03:40.758
- We never have to leave here.
Look around.

03:40.804 --> 03:45.314
Everybody says Jennifer Tilly
has impeccable taste.

03:45.350 --> 03:48.270
- You’re not Jennifer Tilly.

03:48.311 --> 03:51.861
- Another reason why
you can never leave.

03:51.898 --> 03:53.228
[giggles]

03:53.275 --> 03:54.615
[plate clacks]

03:54.651 --> 03:58.111
Now, if you’ll excuse me,
Nica,

03:58.155 --> 04:01.125
I need to speak with him.

04:01.158 --> 04:03.828
[grunting]

04:03.869 --> 04:06.829
[chilling music]

04:06.872 --> 04:13.672
♪ ♪

04:15.088 --> 04:16.258
- [grunts]

04:16.298 --> 04:20.838
♪ ♪

04:20.886 --> 04:23.136
[laughs]

04:23.180 --> 04:24.350
Hiya, doll.

04:24.389 --> 04:26.139
- Hello, Chucky.

04:26.183 --> 04:28.983
What the fuck is this?

04:29.019 --> 04:30.809
- [cackling]

04:30.854 --> 04:32.364
[inhales sharply]

04:32.397 --> 04:36.147
Oh, oh,
I’m coming for you, Tiff.

04:36.193 --> 04:40.153
You only think
I’m stuck in that chair.

04:40.197 --> 04:41.697
You’re gonna pay

04:41.740 --> 04:45.120
for what you did to me, doll.

04:45.160 --> 04:48.120
You and those kids,

04:48.163 --> 04:51.173
you’re all dead.

04:51.208 --> 04:58.008
♪ I’m gonna see you all
rotting in the ground ♪

04:58.048 --> 05:00.878
[laughs]

05:00.926 --> 05:04.386
[cackles]

05:04.429 --> 05:07.349
[playful spooky music]

05:07.390 --> 05:14.480
♪ ♪

05:21.947 --> 05:23.737
- "As Jesus came down
from the mountain

05:23.782 --> 05:25.832
"to meet with his disciples,

05:25.867 --> 05:28.327
"a man beseeched him,
’Teacher..."

05:28.370 --> 05:32.580
- ♪ The one with the power’s
the one with the crown ♪

05:32.624 --> 05:35.754
- "’By an unclean spirit.’"

05:35.794 --> 05:39.844
- ♪ Ashes, ashes,
it all burns down ♪

05:39.881 --> 05:43.301
- "’And does
of unspeakable things.’"

05:43.343 --> 05:47.063
- ♪ Watch what you say
and who you say it to ♪

05:47.097 --> 05:50.677
- "’But I beg you, can you
show my poor boy compassion?’"

05:50.725 --> 05:54.645
- ♪ You never know
who’s sneaking up on you ♪

05:54.688 --> 05:57.018
- "’Is it possible still
to redeem him?’

05:57.065 --> 05:59.185
"Jesus replied,
’Oh, faithless generation,

05:59.234 --> 06:00.944
"’how often must I tell you?

06:00.986 --> 06:05.736
"’Anything is possible
if you choose the Lord.’"

06:05.782 --> 06:07.952
"Then, Jesus rebuked
the unclean spirit.

06:07.993 --> 06:10.243
"I command you,
release this child.

06:10.287 --> 06:12.577
Be gone, and never return!’"

06:14.082 --> 06:17.422
"Then, Jesus took the boy
by the hand, raised him up,

06:17.460 --> 06:18.800
and he was saved."

06:20.213 --> 06:21.923
This is the Gospel of the Lord.

06:21.965 --> 06:24.635
all: Praise be to you,
Lord Jesus Christ.

06:26.011 --> 06:27.511
- So what does it mean?

06:27.554 --> 06:29.264
- ♪ Turncoats and traitors ♪

06:29.306 --> 06:31.806
- It’s a metaphor,

06:31.850 --> 06:33.890
and I just--

06:33.935 --> 06:35.805
I love metaphors.

06:37.480 --> 06:40.400
Sin is a choice.

06:40.442 --> 06:41.902
♪ ♪

06:41.943 --> 06:43.573
- ♪ They sharpen
their knives ♪

06:43.612 --> 06:45.992
- It’s not complicated.

06:46.031 --> 06:47.491
It’s primitive.

06:47.532 --> 06:49.832
It’s that--it’s that devil
on our shoulder

06:49.868 --> 06:54.868
tempting us with sex,
drugs, and whatever.

06:54.915 --> 06:57.885
God is a choice too.

06:59.628 --> 07:01.798
Confession is a choice.

07:03.548 --> 07:05.878
And on God’s team,
every confession

07:05.926 --> 07:09.256
is a victory,
because every confession

07:09.304 --> 07:11.854
is someone who has
made a choice

07:11.890 --> 07:14.560
to take one step closer to God.

07:15.727 --> 07:17.307
And God sure does
love a winner.

07:17.354 --> 07:19.774
[dramatic music]

07:19.814 --> 07:22.404
- I despise sports metaphors.

07:23.735 --> 07:25.865
- Peace be with you.
all: And also with you.

07:25.904 --> 07:28.704
- Let us offer
each other the sign of peace.

07:31.326 --> 07:33.196
- Peace be with you.

07:33.244 --> 07:35.204
Hi, I’m Nadine.

07:35.246 --> 07:37.246
- Hi.

07:37.290 --> 07:39.830
- So what you in for?

07:39.876 --> 07:43.206
- He who eats my flesh and
drinks my blood abides in me,

07:43.254 --> 07:45.344
and I in him.

07:45.382 --> 07:48.222
[organ plays]
[bell chimes]

07:48.259 --> 07:51.549
♪ ♪

07:51.596 --> 07:53.556
- Now what do we do?
Do we go up?

07:53.598 --> 07:55.558
- You Catholic?

07:55.600 --> 07:57.440
- No, I don’t think so.

07:57.477 --> 07:59.097
- Oh, then just
hang here with me.

08:00.772 --> 08:02.232
- You’re a heathen too?

08:02.273 --> 08:05.113
- Oh no, I’m Catholic,
but I sinned this morning.

08:05.151 --> 08:07.361
I can’t take Communion again
until I make my confession

08:07.404 --> 08:09.284
to Father O’Malley.

08:09.322 --> 08:11.072
- What did you do?

08:11.116 --> 08:12.736
♪ ♪

08:12.784 --> 08:14.494
- The body of Christ.
- Amen.

08:14.536 --> 08:21.246
♪ ♪

08:21.292 --> 08:23.592
There. That’s him.

08:23.628 --> 08:25.508
That’s Trevor.

08:25.547 --> 08:28.047
- That altar boy?
- Trust me.

08:28.091 --> 08:30.261
He’s evil,

08:30.301 --> 08:32.761
and he’s brilliant.

08:32.804 --> 08:34.604
He could teach Chucky
a thing or two.

08:34.639 --> 08:36.429
- The body of Christ.

08:39.185 --> 08:41.265
The body of Christ.

08:41.312 --> 08:42.522
- Phones.

08:42.564 --> 08:49.614
♪ ♪

08:52.657 --> 08:54.027
- Children.

08:54.075 --> 08:55.405
♪ ♪

08:55.452 --> 08:57.582
Size four.

08:57.620 --> 09:00.540
- Zero.
- Not here, you’re not.

09:00.582 --> 09:02.672
[eerie music]

09:02.709 --> 09:05.749
- I have to wear this
every day?

09:05.795 --> 09:08.755
- [laughs]
Welcome to my world.

09:08.798 --> 09:11.088
And you’ll have
to brush that hair

09:11.134 --> 09:12.844
and take all the makeup
off your face.

09:12.886 --> 09:14.426
You look like Madonna,

09:14.471 --> 09:17.061
and not the good one.

09:17.098 --> 09:18.308
Ah.

09:18.349 --> 09:19.559
Waist?

09:19.601 --> 09:21.021
- 27.

09:21.061 --> 09:25.151
- Young man,
you’re underweight.

09:25.190 --> 09:26.320
- Thank you.

09:26.357 --> 09:27.977
- Good morning, Father.
- Good morning.

09:28.026 --> 09:29.646
- That was a wonderful homily.

09:29.694 --> 09:31.114
- Thank you.

09:32.489 --> 09:33.819
Hi.

09:35.867 --> 09:39.327
I’m Father Bryce,
headmaster at Incarnate Lord.

09:39.370 --> 09:44.250
You must be Ms. Cross,
Mr. Evans, and Mr. Wheeler.

09:45.710 --> 09:47.960
Do you know why you’re here?

09:48.004 --> 09:50.464
- Because God wants us
to seek forgiveness

09:50.507 --> 09:53.007
and to find our way
back to him.

09:53.051 --> 09:54.801
- Very good, Sister Elizabeth.

09:54.844 --> 09:56.394
- Actually, I told them that.

09:56.429 --> 09:58.679
I met with them when they
arrived this morning.

09:58.723 --> 10:01.273
- Oh Father, I started
cataloguing everything

10:01.309 --> 10:02.689
in the Christmas toy drive.

10:02.727 --> 10:04.187
- I thought
you were doing that.

10:04.229 --> 10:06.189
- It’s still weeks away.

10:06.231 --> 10:08.691
- Well, that’s wonderful,
Sister Elizabeth.

10:08.733 --> 10:10.483
No time like the present.

10:10.527 --> 10:13.697
Sister Ruth, who don’t you go
help Edward in the kitchen?

10:13.738 --> 10:14.818
Sister Catherine
and I will show

10:14.864 --> 10:16.624
these kids to their rooms.

10:16.658 --> 10:17.948
Follow me.

10:17.992 --> 10:20.832
[soft dramatic music]

10:20.870 --> 10:22.870
- By the way, Sister,

10:22.914 --> 10:26.384
we received a new donation
this morning

10:26.417 --> 10:28.207
for your toy drive.

10:28.253 --> 10:30.253
- Oh, how wonderful.

10:30.296 --> 10:32.376
Who from?
- Doesn’t say.

10:32.423 --> 10:35.223
♪ ♪

10:40.265 --> 10:41.355
- What?

10:41.391 --> 10:43.181
- Don’t you see it?

10:43.226 --> 10:45.096
Don’t you see him?

10:45.145 --> 10:46.775
Our Lord’s image,
plain as day,

10:46.813 --> 10:48.813
right here in this doll’s face.

10:50.275 --> 10:54.325
- Didn’t you see his image
in a taco at lunch last week?

10:54.362 --> 10:55.532
- That was different.

10:55.572 --> 10:56.952
- Speaking of tacos,

10:56.990 --> 10:58.870
hadn’t you be getting down
to the kitchen?

11:01.286 --> 11:03.746
- The girls’ dormitory
is here on the second floor.

11:03.788 --> 11:05.328
Boys are up on three.

11:05.373 --> 11:07.753
Officially, you are not
allowed to fraternize,

11:07.792 --> 11:09.212
but I think I finally
convinced Father Bryce

11:09.252 --> 11:11.552
that simply isn’t
realistic these days.

11:11.588 --> 11:14.548
Just make sure you leave your
door open if your male friends

11:14.591 --> 11:16.801
are in your room.

11:16.843 --> 11:18.723
- Don’t worry, we’re all
perfectly safe here

11:18.761 --> 11:21.101
when it comes to Jake
and Devon.

11:21.139 --> 11:22.259
- Oh.

11:28.229 --> 11:29.309
- Hi, roomie.

11:29.355 --> 11:31.475
That bed’s yours.

11:31.524 --> 11:34.494
- I’d actually prefer
the bed closer to the door.

11:34.527 --> 11:35.947
You don’t mind, do you?

11:35.987 --> 11:38.737
- I--I need to be close
to the bathroom on account

11:38.781 --> 11:40.371
of my bladder condition.

11:40.408 --> 11:43.118
- Oh, don’t worry,
she’s doing great.

11:43.161 --> 11:45.871
She hasn’t wet
the bed in weeks.

11:45.914 --> 11:47.964
I’ll let you get settled in.

11:47.999 --> 11:49.289
- Fellas, come on.
[claps]

11:49.334 --> 11:50.754
Let’s pick up the pace.

11:51.836 --> 11:53.456
Boys are up here.

11:53.504 --> 11:55.594
The girls are on two.

11:55.632 --> 11:58.012
No fraternizing
in the girls’ rooms.

11:58.051 --> 12:00.341
No exceptions.
- No problem.

12:01.846 --> 12:03.806
- Young people
today are bombarded

12:03.848 --> 12:06.808
with empty messages of love.

12:06.851 --> 12:08.231
- Hey, Devon,
I think we should keep us

12:08.269 --> 12:10.309
on the down low around here.
- Fuck that.

12:10.355 --> 12:12.865
- Look, Catholics aren’t
exactly down with the gays.

12:12.899 --> 12:14.939
- Avoid temptations
of the opposite sex

12:14.984 --> 12:17.454
until you’re mature
enough to handle

12:17.487 --> 12:18.987
the consequences, you know?

12:19.030 --> 12:20.990
- Look, if we screw up,
they’re gonna send us to juvie.

12:21.032 --> 12:23.032
["Sugar & Spice"
by Boyfriend & Pyra]

12:23.076 --> 12:24.486
- ♪ Sticks and stones
may break my bones, but ♪

12:24.535 --> 12:25.945
- Gentlemen.

12:25.995 --> 12:27.705
- [whispering]
♪ They won’t stop me ♪

12:27.747 --> 12:31.917
♪ Sticks and stones
may break my bones, but ♪

12:31.960 --> 12:33.380
- You’re so pretty.

12:34.837 --> 12:37.047
- Not for long.

12:37.090 --> 12:40.090
- I’ve never been friends
with someone so glam before.

12:40.134 --> 12:42.224
- And now you never will be.

12:42.262 --> 12:43.182
- Oh, please.

12:43.221 --> 12:44.471
You don’t need all that makeup.

12:44.514 --> 12:46.144
You’re just naturally glam.

12:47.392 --> 12:48.852
- No.

12:48.893 --> 12:51.483
I mean, we’re not
going to be friends.

12:51.521 --> 12:53.361
I don’t need any more friends.

12:53.398 --> 12:56.818
They just move away,

12:56.859 --> 12:59.529
get busy,

12:59.570 --> 13:01.320
fall in love,

13:01.364 --> 13:02.954
and they couldn’t
possibly understand what

13:02.991 --> 13:05.831
I’m going through, anyway.

13:05.868 --> 13:08.118
Besides, I don’t plan
on being here very long.

13:09.580 --> 13:11.330
- No one ever does.

13:12.709 --> 13:14.959
- How long have you been here?

13:15.003 --> 13:17.673
- Since seventh grade.

13:17.714 --> 13:20.384
My parents couldn’t control me.

13:20.425 --> 13:21.885
- Really?

13:21.926 --> 13:25.466
♪ ♪

13:25.513 --> 13:27.853
Nadine, why are you here?

13:27.890 --> 13:30.390
- Why are you here, Lexy?

13:30.435 --> 13:33.565
I’ll tell you my secrets
if you tell me yours.

13:33.604 --> 13:35.274
- ♪ Break my bones,
but they won’t stop me ♪

13:35.315 --> 13:36.825
♪ Sticks and stones
may break my bones ♪

13:36.858 --> 13:39.688
- Trust me,
you don’t want to know.

13:39.736 --> 13:44.106
- ♪ Sugar and spice
and everything nice ♪

13:44.157 --> 13:49.407
♪ That’s what I like
and what I’m made of ♪

13:49.454 --> 13:53.464
♪ Nightmares and crimes
and everything grime ♪

13:53.499 --> 13:59.419
♪ That’s what I like
and what I’m made of ♪

13:59.464 --> 14:06.434
♪ ♪

14:10.641 --> 14:13.481
- So we’re roommates.

14:13.519 --> 14:15.099
- I’m sure you boys
are anxious to get

14:15.146 --> 14:18.066
on the straight and narrow,

14:18.107 --> 14:20.897
get your lives back on track,
back on the right track,

14:20.943 --> 14:24.663
back on the fast track to God.

14:24.697 --> 14:27.277
- I just love sports metaphors.

14:27.325 --> 14:29.085
- Me too.

14:29.118 --> 14:30.698
Get those clothes
off and get dressed.

14:30.745 --> 14:31.955
Class starts in ten minutes.

14:31.996 --> 14:34.456
And gentlemen,

14:34.499 --> 14:35.999
don’t be late.

14:37.001 --> 14:38.341
[door shuts]

14:39.670 --> 14:42.800
- [panting]

14:45.593 --> 14:47.473
- Hey.
It’s okay, Jake.

14:47.512 --> 14:48.892
- [sobs]

14:48.930 --> 14:50.560
It’s all my fault.

14:52.350 --> 14:54.640
[crying]
It’s all my fault.

14:54.685 --> 14:56.145
- No, it’s not.

14:56.187 --> 14:59.267
[indistinct chatter]

15:02.443 --> 15:03.533
- Shit.

15:05.822 --> 15:07.452
- You know Trevor?

15:08.825 --> 15:11.375
- Knockoff Draco Malfoy?

15:11.411 --> 15:13.501
Unfortunately.

15:13.538 --> 15:15.328
[sighs]
Okay.

15:15.373 --> 15:17.423
I just need
to come out swinging.

15:17.458 --> 15:19.788
Show him who’s boss.

15:19.836 --> 15:21.206
[door creaks]

15:21.254 --> 15:24.214
[suspenseful music]

15:30.763 --> 15:33.353
Hi.
I’m Lexy.

15:33.391 --> 15:35.351
I’m an old friend of Trevor’s.

15:35.393 --> 15:38.023
Hey, did you know he was
born with only one testicle?

15:38.062 --> 15:40.312
- [stifles laughter]
- [chuckles]

15:40.356 --> 15:42.726
Or so he told me
in fourth grade.

15:42.775 --> 15:44.895
- And you promised
you’d never tell.

15:44.944 --> 15:46.704
- Oops.

15:46.737 --> 15:47.817
- Look, Alexandra.

15:47.864 --> 15:49.374
- Lexy.

15:49.407 --> 15:50.657
- Lexy.

15:50.700 --> 15:53.120
I made your life a living
hell back in the day,

15:53.161 --> 15:55.661
and for that I’m truly sorry.

15:55.705 --> 15:57.125
I hope you can forgive me.

15:57.165 --> 15:59.005
For what it’s worth,
I’m not the same person

15:59.041 --> 16:00.881
as I was back then.

16:02.420 --> 16:04.340
- So who are you?

16:04.380 --> 16:07.380
- Someone who’s not ashamed
of having only one testicle,

16:07.425 --> 16:08.515
I guess.

16:08.551 --> 16:10.391
- Banish anxiety
from your heart

16:10.428 --> 16:12.388
and cast off
the troubles of your body.

16:12.430 --> 16:14.720
- For youth and vigor
are meaningless.

16:14.765 --> 16:17.095
- Ecclesiastes 11:10.

16:17.143 --> 16:19.103
- I can only imagine
what you’ve gone through

16:19.145 --> 16:20.775
this past year.

16:20.813 --> 16:22.023
Everyone’s talking about it.

16:22.064 --> 16:23.614
All those murders.

16:23.649 --> 16:25.859
Dating a deranged killer

16:25.902 --> 16:29.862
and that poor soul
taken in your own home...

16:29.906 --> 16:32.066
but I think the Lord
brought you here

16:32.116 --> 16:34.656
so I can finally
make things right with you.

16:34.702 --> 16:37.332
And I thank God
for the opportunity.

16:37.371 --> 16:40.581
It’d be a sin to waste it.

16:40.625 --> 16:42.505
Peace be with you.

16:42.543 --> 16:45.503
[eerie music]

16:45.546 --> 16:47.546
- You can see how
Hieronymus Bosch,

16:47.590 --> 16:50.970
in his typical surrealist mode,
depicts the seven deadly sins,

16:51.010 --> 16:55.720
starting with wrath at bottom,
and then moving clockwise,

16:55.765 --> 16:58.485
we get envy,

16:58.518 --> 16:59.888
greed,

16:59.936 --> 17:01.846
gluttony,

17:01.896 --> 17:03.396
sloth,

17:03.439 --> 17:04.899
lust,

17:04.941 --> 17:07.031
and finally, pride.

17:08.319 --> 17:09.899
Can anyone tell me
what the outer four

17:09.946 --> 17:11.276
circles represent,

17:11.322 --> 17:13.372
the so-called
"last four things"?

17:13.407 --> 17:14.447
Jake.

17:14.492 --> 17:17.792
- They represent
the four wages of sin:

17:17.828 --> 17:22.118
death, judgement,
heaven, and hell.

17:22.166 --> 17:23.576
- That’s very good, Jake.

17:23.626 --> 17:25.086
You’re familiar
with the surrealists.

17:25.127 --> 17:26.297
- A little.

17:26.337 --> 17:29.127
I’m more familiar
with the wages of sin.

17:29.173 --> 17:30.513
- But why should we,
as Catholics,

17:30.550 --> 17:32.470
need to worry about this
if we can just

17:32.510 --> 17:34.760
go to confession
and be forgiven?

17:34.804 --> 17:37.474
- I’m gonna let you guys
in on a little secret.

17:37.515 --> 17:39.645
You know, despite what
Father Bryce said in his homily

17:39.684 --> 17:43.944
this morning, in my experience,
sin isn’t really simple.

17:43.980 --> 17:46.650
It’s actually
super complicated.

17:46.691 --> 17:48.231
Good people do bad things

17:48.276 --> 17:50.776
for all kinds
of screwed-up reasons.

17:50.820 --> 17:53.450
It’s important for all of us
to examine those reasons

17:53.489 --> 17:56.489
and not treat confession
like a hot shower.

17:56.534 --> 17:58.494
Redemption can’t really happen

17:58.536 --> 18:01.036
without a long, hard look
in the mirror.

18:02.665 --> 18:04.585
Any more questions?

18:06.544 --> 18:11.804
- Are there any sins that
are just...unforgivable?

18:11.841 --> 18:13.971
- Well, I sure hope not,

18:14.010 --> 18:15.970
because then
I’m really in trouble.

18:16.012 --> 18:17.852
[laughter]

18:17.888 --> 18:20.718
Okay, page 43.

18:20.766 --> 18:27.686
♪ ♪

18:44.707 --> 18:51.457
♪ ♪

18:51.505 --> 18:53.665
- Hi.
I’m Chucky.

18:53.716 --> 18:56.886
Wanna play?
- Not particularly.

18:56.927 --> 19:03.727
♪ ♪

19:19.241 --> 19:21.701
[footsteps]

19:23.037 --> 19:26.117
- Boo!
- [screaming]

19:29.085 --> 19:31.255
- [chuckling]
Oh, stop.

19:31.295 --> 19:33.915
Really?
Just looking at me

19:33.964 --> 19:35.924
is scary enough
to give you a heart attack?

19:35.966 --> 19:37.046
- [out of breath]
Oh, God.

19:37.093 --> 19:39.933
- Oh, my God, thank you!

19:39.970 --> 19:41.640
You made my day.

19:41.681 --> 19:43.271
[laughing]

19:43.307 --> 19:44.387
Wait.
Wait, wait, wait.

19:44.433 --> 19:46.853
That’s vampires, right?

19:46.894 --> 19:49.404
[snarling]

19:50.481 --> 19:53.071
[tense choir music]

19:53.109 --> 19:54.819
♪ ♪

19:54.860 --> 19:57.280
Hi. I’m Chucky.

19:57.321 --> 20:00.071
Wanna pray?

20:00.116 --> 20:01.276
- [grunts]

20:01.325 --> 20:04.285
- [cackling]

20:04.328 --> 20:07.958
♪ ♪

20:07.998 --> 20:10.828
[cackling]

20:12.837 --> 20:14.247
[camera clicks]

20:14.255 --> 20:24.315
[bell tolling]

20:25.433 --> 20:28.103
[dramatic music]

20:28.144 --> 20:31.154
♪ ♪

20:31.188 --> 20:32.398
- Shit.

20:32.440 --> 20:39.280
♪ ♪

20:41.490 --> 20:43.580
- [gasps]

20:43.617 --> 20:44.697
- Shit.

20:44.744 --> 20:47.164
- Look at him.
He’s taunting us.

20:48.748 --> 20:50.288
- He isn’t doing anything.

20:50.332 --> 20:53.212
- That’s what I mean.
It’s diabolical.

20:53.252 --> 20:56.212
[ominous music]

20:56.255 --> 21:03.135
♪ ♪

21:04.513 --> 21:05.973
[keys jangle]

21:10.978 --> 21:13.018
- Could I have
your attention, please?

21:14.315 --> 21:17.195
Sister Elizabeth
has been called home.

21:17.234 --> 21:18.744
God rest her soul.

21:18.778 --> 21:20.988
all: God rest her soul.

21:21.030 --> 21:23.120
- Apparently,
it was a heart attack.

21:23.908 --> 21:27.038
Now, I know you’ll all
keep her in your prayers,

21:27.077 --> 21:31.497
but the best way to honor her
is by honoring God.

21:31.540 --> 21:35.090
So let’s get back to class,
and let’s get busy.

21:35.127 --> 21:38.297
Idle hands
are the Devil’s playground.

21:38.339 --> 21:40.299
I will be taking
the sister’s classes

21:40.341 --> 21:43.181
for the rest of the day,
starting with study hall.

21:43.219 --> 21:44.639
Thank you.

21:44.678 --> 21:45.888
Okay.

21:45.930 --> 21:48.680
- Okay.
Children, to class.

21:48.724 --> 21:51.444
- I can talk to you guys now.

21:51.477 --> 21:54.437
[tense music]

21:54.480 --> 22:00.650
♪ ♪

22:00.694 --> 22:02.534
- What do we do?

22:02.571 --> 22:04.031
- We can’t tell anyone.

22:04.073 --> 22:05.413
They’ll lock us
in a mental hospital

22:05.449 --> 22:06.659
and throw away the key.

22:06.700 --> 22:07.990
- I say we make a run for it.

22:08.035 --> 22:09.825
I mean, this isn’t a gulag.

22:09.870 --> 22:11.330
There are no armed guards.

22:11.372 --> 22:14.542
We’re not gonna get
shot or anything.

22:14.583 --> 22:16.503
Right?

22:16.544 --> 22:17.924
- We have nowhere else to go.

22:17.962 --> 22:19.922
So let’s just
stand our ground,

22:19.964 --> 22:21.424
give Chucky what’s
coming to him.

22:21.465 --> 22:24.005
- This is all my fault.
If I never bought the fucker

22:24.051 --> 22:25.261
at the yard sale
in the first place,

22:25.302 --> 22:27.102
none of this
would have happened.

22:27.137 --> 22:30.717
My dad, your dad, your mom,

22:30.766 --> 22:32.016
Gary.

22:32.059 --> 22:34.059
- Jake, stop blaming
yourself, okay?

22:34.103 --> 22:36.193
Chucky did it.
He’s the asshole here.

22:36.230 --> 22:39.900
- I can’t let anyone else die,
especially you guys.

22:40.985 --> 22:42.745
I have to get in there.

22:43.988 --> 22:45.408
- You people lost?

22:46.740 --> 22:48.580
- No, Father.

22:48.617 --> 22:51.407
- Look, I know your history.

22:53.581 --> 22:55.291
Dr. Mixter filled me in.

22:58.878 --> 23:01.208
It’s just a doll.

23:03.841 --> 23:05.721
I’ll see you three
in study hall.

23:06.760 --> 23:08.260
Now.

23:08.304 --> 23:12.814
♪ ♪

23:12.850 --> 23:15.520
- That guy reminds me
of my dad.

23:18.522 --> 23:19.942
- Yes.
- Yes!

23:19.982 --> 23:21.732
- No!
- [laughs]

23:21.775 --> 23:24.895
"If I get sole
custody of the kids,

23:24.945 --> 23:28.065
that’s another
10 grand in child support."

23:28.115 --> 23:29.735
- You just won $11 million!
- Hey!

23:29.783 --> 23:31.123
- Hey!
- Hey!

23:31.160 --> 23:32.990
- I’m the victim here.
- "I’m the victim here!

23:33.037 --> 23:34.957
"You said it yourself.

23:34.997 --> 23:37.707
Now, I’m gonna hit
him where it hurts!"

23:37.750 --> 23:39.500
[laughing]

23:39.543 --> 23:42.213
"Hit him where it hurts."

23:42.254 --> 23:44.634
- You do realize
that that’s not you.

23:44.673 --> 23:46.433
- Of course.

23:46.467 --> 23:51.557
Jennifer Tilly did this role
long before I took over.

23:51.597 --> 23:52.887
- This is just sad.

23:52.932 --> 23:53.932
- What?

23:53.974 --> 23:55.644
- This--sitting here,

23:55.684 --> 23:58.354
watching old Jennifer Tilly
movies over and over.

23:58.395 --> 24:01.515
When was the last
time you booked a job?

24:01.565 --> 24:04.435
- Nica, I told you,

24:04.485 --> 24:07.905
we have everything we need
right here in this house.

24:07.947 --> 24:09.067
- Yeah, but at
the rate you’re going,

24:09.114 --> 24:10.874
you’re gonna lose this house.

24:10.908 --> 24:12.118
I know you went through

24:12.159 --> 24:15.249
all of Jennifer Tilly’s
"Simpsons" money.

24:15.287 --> 24:16.497
- [chuckles]

24:16.538 --> 24:20.458
- How does someone go
through $100 million?

24:20.501 --> 24:22.881
- It’s not easy being me.

24:22.920 --> 24:25.960
It’s not cheap being me either.

24:26.006 --> 24:28.006
- Bullshit!
Bullshit!

24:29.426 --> 24:32.176
You know, when you
first brought me here,

24:32.221 --> 24:33.891
I thought-I thought
I was gonna be

24:33.931 --> 24:36.891
living with a real movie star.
- Mm.

24:36.934 --> 24:39.314
- Some glamorous and exciting.

24:42.106 --> 24:44.066
Instead, I got this.

24:45.442 --> 24:49.152
I got you--
a washed up imposter,

24:49.196 --> 24:51.026
obsessed with
her own fake past.

24:53.534 --> 24:58.004
You need to get out of this
house and get a job, Tiffany.

24:58.038 --> 25:00.458
- [laughs]
So you can escape?

25:00.499 --> 25:01.999
Nice try, Nica.

25:02.042 --> 25:04.502
- How the fuck am I
gonna escape?

25:04.545 --> 25:06.715
- Oh, that reminds me,

25:06.755 --> 25:10.675
my darling Glen and Glenda
are coming by this weekend

25:10.718 --> 25:15.308
for their birthday celebration,
so you know the drill.

25:15.347 --> 25:19.097
It’s either the ball gag
or the chloroform.

25:19.143 --> 25:20.443
Your choice.

25:20.477 --> 25:23.727
Oh shit,
we’re all out of chloroform.

25:23.772 --> 25:25.322
How did that happen?

25:26.483 --> 25:28.743
[doorbell rings]

25:28.777 --> 25:31.607
Oh my god.
That’s not the gate.

25:31.655 --> 25:33.525
It’s the front door.

25:33.574 --> 25:35.874
- Help!
Help me!

25:35.909 --> 25:37.039
- Shh.
- Help me!

25:37.077 --> 25:38.947
- Shh. Shh.
- Please help!

25:38.996 --> 25:41.746
- Shh. Shh.
You’re gonna ruin everything.

25:41.790 --> 25:44.460
What is wrong with you?
Shh.

25:47.337 --> 25:50.297
- [cries]

25:54.636 --> 25:56.556
- H--Hello?

25:56.597 --> 25:59.427
- Oh, my God.

25:59.475 --> 26:00.985
Ms. Tilly,

26:01.018 --> 26:05.358
I am sorry to bother you,
but I am a huge fan.

26:05.397 --> 26:07.937
- H-how did you get
past the gate?

26:07.983 --> 26:09.533
- I climbed over the wall.

26:09.568 --> 26:11.648
- Well, this is
private property.

26:11.695 --> 26:13.145
I’m calling the cops.

26:13.197 --> 26:16.577
- Oh, Detective Sam Gavin.

26:16.617 --> 26:17.827
- Oh.

26:17.868 --> 26:21.038
- Beverly Hills Police,
but I’m also a fan.

26:21.080 --> 26:24.170
- Okay.
Well, in that case,

26:24.208 --> 26:27.708
Officer, maybe you would
like to take a selfie with me?

26:27.753 --> 26:30.763
- Detective, and,
you know, I would love that.

26:30.798 --> 26:33.968
But I’m actually here
because of a missing person.

26:34.009 --> 26:35.509
Ms. Tilly, have
you ever heard--

26:35.552 --> 26:37.012
- No.

26:37.054 --> 26:38.934
- Ms. Tilly,
have you ever heard--

26:38.972 --> 26:42.682
- No. No. No. No.

26:42.726 --> 26:44.936
- Ms. Tilly, have you
ever heard of Nica Pierce?

26:44.978 --> 26:47.938
- Oh!

26:47.981 --> 26:49.691
Nica Pierce.

26:49.733 --> 26:52.193
Yes, I believe I met her

26:52.236 --> 26:56.236
when I visited that
mental hospital back east.

26:56.281 --> 26:59.241
You know, that’s
one of the causes

26:59.284 --> 27:01.624
I’m most passionate about--

27:01.662 --> 27:05.172
women with
mental health issues.

27:05.207 --> 27:07.077
- Then you’re aware that--
- No.

27:07.126 --> 27:08.996
- Well, shortly
after your visit...

27:09.044 --> 27:11.094
- Uh-huh.
- She killed several people.

27:11.130 --> 27:13.130
- Oh! Oh! Oh!

27:13.173 --> 27:14.763
- And then she escaped.

27:14.800 --> 27:17.510
- I can’t believe
they’d be stupid enough

27:17.553 --> 27:19.853
to let her escape.

27:19.888 --> 27:23.058
Well--oh, you’re still here.

27:23.100 --> 27:24.390
I mean--

27:24.434 --> 27:26.944
- Yeah--
- Okay, bye.

27:26.979 --> 27:29.859
[suspenseful music]

27:29.898 --> 27:34.988
♪ ♪

27:35.028 --> 27:37.158
- Yes, Mr. Wheeler?

27:37.197 --> 27:38.697
- Can I use the restroom?

27:39.867 --> 27:41.657
- I don’t know, can you?

27:41.702 --> 27:44.332
"May I go to
the restroom, Father?"

27:44.371 --> 27:45.501
- May I?

27:52.546 --> 27:55.256
- You have exactly
five minutes.

27:55.299 --> 27:56.549
- Five minutes?

28:00.679 --> 28:02.469
- Jake, you can’t just--

28:07.686 --> 28:09.226
- You two can wait.

28:10.814 --> 28:13.234
One pass, zero mischief.

28:13.275 --> 28:16.245
[eerie music]

28:16.278 --> 28:23.408
♪ ♪

28:36.048 --> 28:43.218
♪ ♪

29:10.165 --> 29:11.875
- All right,
you fucking asshole.

29:11.917 --> 29:13.077
- Really, Mr. Wheeler?

29:13.126 --> 29:15.796
[dramatic music]

29:15.837 --> 29:17.047
Back in the old days,

29:17.089 --> 29:18.969
we would have washed
your mouth out with soap.

29:19.007 --> 29:21.587
♪ ♪

29:21.635 --> 29:24.105
We have different methods
of teaching lessons now.

29:24.137 --> 29:28.267
♪ ♪

29:28.267 --> 29:37.777
- You’ve suffered great
pain in your young life,

29:37.818 --> 29:41.738
but you’ve also
caused great pain.

29:41.780 --> 29:43.870
You know why?
- I’m sure you’ll tell me.

29:43.907 --> 29:45.237
- Because you’re lost

29:45.284 --> 29:48.334
like every other kid that
comes through my door,

29:48.370 --> 29:50.460
but this place isn’t
a prison, Jake.

29:50.497 --> 29:53.327
Here, you don’t have to be
an orphan anymore.

29:53.375 --> 29:56.345
You can choose
to be a son again,

29:56.378 --> 29:58.668
of the Heavenly Father.

29:58.714 --> 30:04.224
Lay down your burdens and
let Him do the heavy lifting.

30:04.261 --> 30:08.221
Just let go...

30:08.265 --> 30:11.065
and let God.

30:11.101 --> 30:13.521
All you gotta do
is stop fighting.

30:13.562 --> 30:15.362
- I’ll never stop fighting.

30:15.397 --> 30:18.357
[dramatic music]

30:18.400 --> 30:25.410
♪ ♪

30:31.413 --> 30:33.083
- [exhales]

30:33.123 --> 30:36.383
[suspenseful music]

30:36.418 --> 30:39.378
♪ ♪

30:39.421 --> 30:42.051
Your first Bible is
something you’ll never forget.

30:42.090 --> 30:44.010
I remember my father
calling me into his study,

30:44.051 --> 30:46.761
which usually meant
I was in a world of trouble.

30:46.803 --> 30:50.143
But on this day,
he handed me the good book,

30:50.182 --> 30:53.142
and he said, "Son, I want you
to flip through these pages

30:53.185 --> 30:55.985
"until you find a passage
that speaks to you.

30:56.021 --> 30:58.111
"And then,
I want you to come back,

30:58.148 --> 31:00.398
and I want you
to read it to me."

31:06.198 --> 31:10.948
I spent many nights
with my father after that...

31:10.994 --> 31:12.954
going through
these sacred lessons.

31:12.996 --> 31:15.416
Some of the best
memories of my life.

31:17.584 --> 31:19.134
This is yours now.

31:19.169 --> 31:21.499
It’s time for you to find
a passage that speaks to you.

31:21.546 --> 31:24.126
[eerie music]

31:24.174 --> 31:26.594
- Wait. Wait. What?

31:27.469 --> 31:30.809
- I’ll check with you
at the end of the period.

31:30.847 --> 31:32.717
Maybe you could
read me something.

31:32.766 --> 31:35.096
- You can’t just leave me here.

31:37.979 --> 31:39.939
- Do the work, Jake.

31:41.483 --> 31:43.363
You won’t regret it.

31:43.402 --> 31:48.822
♪ ♪

31:50.492 --> 31:51.532
- Wait.

31:53.662 --> 31:56.332
[panting]

31:56.373 --> 31:58.673
♪ ♪

31:58.708 --> 32:01.588
[footsteps]

32:05.715 --> 32:07.375
- Thank you, Sister.
- Father.

32:09.636 --> 32:10.886
- Yes, Mr. Evans.

32:10.929 --> 32:12.509
- I was just wondering
where Jake is.

32:18.728 --> 32:19.848
- Why is that?

32:19.896 --> 32:20.976
- Well, he said
I could look at his notes

32:21.022 --> 32:22.442
from the sermon this morning.

32:22.482 --> 32:24.322
- The homily.

32:24.359 --> 32:26.609
- Right. Right.
Homily.

32:26.653 --> 32:28.153
- Well, that’s
very charitable of him,

32:28.196 --> 32:29.696
but you’re gonna have to wait.

32:29.739 --> 32:30.989
- Where is he?

32:31.032 --> 32:32.912
- He’s exactly
where he should be.

32:32.951 --> 32:33.911
And so are you.

32:33.952 --> 32:39.872
♪ ♪

32:39.916 --> 32:41.876
- Okay.

32:41.918 --> 32:43.628
It’s just us now.

32:45.297 --> 32:47.417
How many of you
survived that crash?

32:47.466 --> 32:49.926
♪ ♪

32:49.968 --> 32:51.178
Oh, come on.
This is stupid.

32:51.219 --> 32:53.389
I know it’s you.
Just talk to me.

32:55.098 --> 32:57.138
All right.
Have it your way.

32:57.184 --> 33:04.194
♪ ♪

33:09.571 --> 33:10.911
[camera clicks]

33:10.947 --> 33:13.197
- Gotcha.
[laughs]

33:13.241 --> 33:15.911
[dramatic music]

33:15.952 --> 33:17.542
♪ ♪

33:17.579 --> 33:19.539
[laughs]

33:19.581 --> 33:25.921
♪ ♪

33:27.881 --> 33:30.051
- Where’s the doll?

33:30.091 --> 33:32.141
- I honestly have no idea.

33:40.977 --> 33:42.477
- Did you even open it?

33:43.939 --> 33:45.399
Open.

33:49.152 --> 33:51.242
Turn to John 8:44.

33:54.991 --> 33:57.081
Read it to me.

33:57.118 --> 33:59.078
Loud and clear.

33:59.120 --> 34:01.580
- [sighs]

34:01.623 --> 34:04.293
"You are from
your father, the Devil,

34:04.334 --> 34:06.964
"and you choose to do
your father’s desires.

34:07.003 --> 34:08.463
"He was a murderer
from the beginning

34:08.505 --> 34:10.015
"and does not stand
in the truth,

34:10.048 --> 34:11.588
"because there
is no truth in him.

34:11.633 --> 34:15.053
"When he lies, he speaks
according to his own nature,

34:15.095 --> 34:19.105
for he is a liar,
and the father of lies."

34:19.140 --> 34:21.680
- I encourage you to
choose the right father.

34:24.354 --> 34:26.154
Now, where is the doll?

34:26.189 --> 34:28.149
- I told you, I don’t know.

34:31.903 --> 34:33.283
Can I go now?

34:35.031 --> 34:36.531
- Thank God.

34:46.084 --> 34:48.094
What happened?

34:48.128 --> 34:49.548
- He got away.

34:51.673 --> 34:53.223
- Shit!

34:54.467 --> 34:57.257
- He took my picture.
- What?

34:57.304 --> 34:59.764
- He had this phone,
and he took my picture

34:59.806 --> 35:01.346
and he ran up the chimney.

35:04.686 --> 35:07.306
Didn’t even try
to hurt me or anything.

35:07.355 --> 35:10.015
- Why would he do that?
- No idea.

35:10.066 --> 35:11.356
- Great.

35:11.401 --> 35:13.861
Another killer doll
with a shady plan.

35:13.903 --> 35:16.203
’Cause that worked out
so well the last time.

35:16.239 --> 35:18.069
- Whatever he’s doing,
we have to find him fast.

35:18.116 --> 35:20.116
[eerie music]

35:20.118 --> 35:27.788
[ominous music]

35:27.834 --> 35:29.214
- There’s no lock?

35:29.252 --> 35:31.212
- They only lock
from the outside.

35:31.254 --> 35:32.714
School policy.

35:32.756 --> 35:39.886
♪ ♪

35:41.765 --> 35:43.565
What are you doing?

35:43.600 --> 35:46.390
- What the hell
is all this shit?

35:48.438 --> 35:51.518
- Look, I--

35:51.566 --> 35:53.316
I steal things sometimes.

35:55.403 --> 35:57.203
That’s why I’m here.

35:58.782 --> 36:01.242
The really good stuff
is under the bed.

36:01.284 --> 36:04.874
- I mean, everyone’s
got their secrets.

36:05.955 --> 36:07.915
- What’s your secret?

36:07.957 --> 36:09.747
- My mother is the antichrist.

36:09.793 --> 36:11.793
- Moms are the worst.

36:20.136 --> 36:22.386
- Here. Help me move this
in front of the door.

36:22.430 --> 36:25.060
- Why would we be moving the
dresser in front of the door?

36:26.601 --> 36:28.191
- Because I sleepwalk.

36:28.228 --> 36:29.598
- Cool.

36:32.565 --> 36:34.565
Hey, that’s your thing.

36:34.609 --> 36:36.439
- My thing?

36:36.486 --> 36:38.066
- Your secret.

36:39.989 --> 36:41.949
- Yeah. Right.

36:41.991 --> 36:43.451
Don’t tell anyone.

36:43.493 --> 36:45.293
- Cross my heart.

36:45.328 --> 36:52.248
♪ ♪

37:18.069 --> 37:25.199
♪ ♪

37:50.602 --> 37:52.022
[camera clicks]

37:52.061 --> 37:57.361
♪ ♪

37:57.400 --> 37:59.360
- [sniffs]

38:00.570 --> 38:01.900
[coughs]

38:01.946 --> 38:05.366
♪ ♪

38:05.408 --> 38:08.368
[scraping]

38:08.411 --> 38:15.331
♪ ♪

38:16.753 --> 38:19.593
- [screams]
- [screams]

38:22.592 --> 38:24.892
- [screams]

38:24.928 --> 38:26.718
- [screams]

38:26.763 --> 38:29.893
- [screams]

38:33.436 --> 38:34.726
- Lexy!

38:34.771 --> 38:37.401
[dramatic music]

38:37.440 --> 38:43.450
♪ ♪

38:43.488 --> 38:46.738
- What’s going on?
- [gasping]

38:46.783 --> 38:48.203
- Nadine.
- Open this door.

38:48.243 --> 38:49.873
- Now, I know this is intense,
and you may be wondering

38:49.911 --> 38:51.161
what’s going on--

38:51.204 --> 38:52.414
- I know exactly
what’s going on.

38:52.455 --> 38:54.955
God’s punishing me
for being a klepto,

38:54.999 --> 38:56.579
but I found the doll
in the stairwell.

38:56.626 --> 38:58.246
He was a ginger just like me.
- I know.

38:58.294 --> 38:59.594
- And he was just so adorable

38:59.629 --> 39:01.259
that I couldn’t
help by myself and--

39:01.297 --> 39:03.257
- You need to listen
to me, okay?

39:03.299 --> 39:05.589
Say nothing.
- But--

39:05.635 --> 39:07.055
- Nothing!

39:08.012 --> 39:09.432
[people muttering]

39:09.472 --> 39:11.312
- I want to know
what’s going on right now.

39:12.600 --> 39:15.020
- Of course.
What would you like to know?

39:15.061 --> 39:17.151
- Why were you screaming?

39:18.773 --> 39:21.193
- Because I was scared.
- Scared of what?

39:21.234 --> 39:23.324
- What’s going on here?
What’s happening?

39:25.947 --> 39:27.987
- I was scared of...

39:28.032 --> 39:35.122
♪ ♪

39:38.835 --> 39:39.965
Bathroom.

39:42.046 --> 39:43.296
- You were scared
of the bathroom?

39:43.339 --> 39:44.419
- No.

39:45.633 --> 39:46.973
No.

39:49.804 --> 39:54.644
I was scared of never seeing
my old bathroom again.

39:54.684 --> 39:57.654
[eerie music]

39:57.687 --> 40:00.977
♪ ♪

40:01.024 --> 40:03.654
- Okay.
- It was a great bathroom.

40:03.693 --> 40:05.153
- You’re lucky to have a
bathroom at all, young lady.

40:05.194 --> 40:07.494
- Sister, please.

40:08.907 --> 40:10.197
You’ll do well here,

40:10.241 --> 40:13.491
and if you’re open
to God’s teachings...

40:13.536 --> 40:20.456
♪ ♪

40:22.086 --> 40:24.506
- [panting]

40:35.767 --> 40:38.347
♪ ♪

40:38.394 --> 40:40.154
- Where the hell could he be?

40:41.105 --> 40:42.685
- I have no idea.

40:45.485 --> 40:47.535
- [screams]
- Jake!

40:47.570 --> 40:50.700
[chilling music]

40:50.740 --> 40:51.910
- [screams]
[grunts]

40:51.950 --> 40:53.030
[knife clatters]

40:53.076 --> 40:54.116
[groans]

40:54.160 --> 40:58.870
♪ ♪

40:58.915 --> 41:00.715
[screams]

41:00.750 --> 41:02.210
Oh.

41:02.251 --> 41:04.381
Get off me, you brute!

41:05.505 --> 41:06.845
Get off!

41:06.881 --> 41:08.221
- What are you doing here?

41:08.257 --> 41:10.217
- That’s for me to know
and you to find out.

41:11.594 --> 41:13.224
- Why’d you take
Jake’s picture?

41:13.262 --> 41:15.262
- Picture?
What picture?

41:15.306 --> 41:17.136
I don’t know what
you’re talking about.

41:17.183 --> 41:19.893
♪ ♪

41:19.936 --> 41:21.226
- How many of you are left?

41:21.270 --> 41:24.730
- Fuck you.
I’m not telling you shit.

41:24.774 --> 41:25.984
[spits]

41:26.025 --> 41:27.565
[laughs]

41:27.610 --> 41:29.400
- Hey!

41:29.445 --> 41:31.405
I think I know what
Chucky’s up to.

41:31.406 --> 41:38.946
- Does he eat?

41:38.997 --> 41:40.957
- I think so.

41:40.999 --> 41:42.579
- Does he sleep?

41:42.625 --> 41:44.745
- I have no idea.

41:44.794 --> 41:46.924
- So, does he, like,
go to the bathroom?

41:48.339 --> 41:50.469
- God, I hope not.

41:51.509 --> 41:53.049
There they are.

41:53.094 --> 41:55.354
[eerie music]

41:55.388 --> 41:56.508
♪ ♪

41:56.556 --> 41:58.056
What happened?
Did you get him?

42:00.852 --> 42:03.772
She knows.
It’s okay, she’s cool.

42:05.273 --> 42:06.903
So is he dead or what?

42:08.818 --> 42:10.778
- We have something
to show you.

42:10.820 --> 42:12.450
Come on.

42:12.488 --> 42:15.448
[dramatic music]

42:15.491 --> 42:20.701
♪ ♪

42:20.747 --> 42:22.997
- What the hell?
Why didn’t you kill him?

42:23.041 --> 42:24.421
- Think about it.

42:24.459 --> 42:26.249
Ever since he got here,
Chucky’s been acting weird.

42:26.294 --> 42:27.674
- Mm-mm.
- He took pictures of me.

42:27.712 --> 42:29.052
He’s been taking pictures
all over the school.

42:29.088 --> 42:30.798
And every chance he
got to kill one of us,

42:30.840 --> 42:32.840
he ran away instead.
Why?

42:32.884 --> 42:34.724
- Because that’s not his job.

42:34.761 --> 42:37.511
- Exactly.
This Chucky isn’t an assassin.

42:37.555 --> 42:39.845
He’s a scout.
- Like a Boy Scout?

42:39.891 --> 42:41.101
- Mm.

42:41.142 --> 42:43.142
- No, like--
like a scout in war.

42:43.186 --> 42:44.976
He’s collecting
information for someone.

42:45.021 --> 42:47.111
- [muffled speech]

42:47.148 --> 42:48.818
- Who?

42:48.858 --> 42:50.398
- That’s what we’re
gonna find out.

42:50.443 --> 42:52.323
- [muffled speech]

42:52.361 --> 42:55.321
[tense music]

42:55.364 --> 42:57.244
[oven door squeaks]

42:57.283 --> 42:58.703
- Ahh.

43:03.247 --> 43:05.457
- I love birthdays, don’t you?

43:05.500 --> 43:06.790
[alarm beeps]

43:06.834 --> 43:09.924
Oh, oh, oh, oh, oh!
That’s the gate!

43:11.798 --> 43:13.878
[buzzer buzzes]
[laughs]

43:13.925 --> 43:16.895
They’re here!
The twins are here!

43:16.928 --> 43:18.638
[elevator dings]

43:18.679 --> 43:21.889
- Tiffany, Tiffany,
you don’t need to do this.

43:21.933 --> 43:24.183
- It’s not that
I don’t trust you,

43:24.227 --> 43:28.187
but I still don’t know how
that head got inside my bed.

43:28.231 --> 43:30.441
- What?
What are you talking about?

43:30.483 --> 43:33.573
- I’m talking about Chucky.
[laughs]

43:33.611 --> 43:35.031
Maybe the two of you

43:35.071 --> 43:37.321
are talking about me
behind my back.

43:37.365 --> 43:40.585
Maybe the two of you
are plotting against me

43:40.618 --> 43:43.618
deep inside that
pretty little head of yours.

43:43.663 --> 43:47.043
[laughs]
Okay.

43:47.083 --> 43:48.713
Shh. Shh. Shh.

43:48.751 --> 43:51.551
[dramatic music]

43:51.587 --> 43:52.917
[doorbell rings]

43:52.964 --> 43:54.474
Coming!

43:54.507 --> 43:57.007
I’m coming!
I’m coming!

44:02.348 --> 44:04.058
Hi.
- Hi.

44:04.100 --> 44:08.150
Remember me?
Detective Sam Gavin?

44:08.187 --> 44:10.647
I’m sorry to bother
you again, Ms. Tilly,

44:10.690 --> 44:13.320
but something’s
just not adding up.

44:13.359 --> 44:19.239
♪ ♪

44:19.991 --> 44:22.741
- I think she’s starting
to suspect something.

44:22.785 --> 44:28.955
♪ ♪

44:29.000 --> 44:31.750
- If she finds out
we’re working together,

44:31.794 --> 44:33.254
it’s all over.

44:33.296 --> 44:35.916
- Listen, asshole,
the only reason

44:35.965 --> 44:39.395
I even tolerate you being
here is because I have to.

44:39.427 --> 44:42.967
- After all we’ve been through?
Come on, Nica.

44:43.014 --> 44:45.224
Admit it.
I’m growing on you.

44:45.266 --> 44:46.516
- Like leprosy.

44:46.559 --> 44:49.309
- You need me
if we’re gonna get out of here.

44:49.353 --> 44:54.573
- What I really need is I need
to get you out of my head.

44:58.946 --> 45:02.986
And I need to Tiffany
to get what’s coming to her.

45:03.034 --> 45:07.544
- You see, Nica?
We do have something in common.

45:07.580 --> 45:12.500
♪ ♪

45:12.543 --> 45:16.093
- I think Nica Pierce is here.

45:20.009 --> 45:21.929
- Oh!

45:21.969 --> 45:25.009
You’re right, Officer,
Nica Pierce is here,

45:25.056 --> 45:27.806
but she’s innocent, I swear.

45:27.850 --> 45:31.020
- That’s not for us
to decide, Jennifer.

45:31.062 --> 45:33.732
- Ms. Tilly.
- Ms. Tilly.

45:36.442 --> 45:38.652
- I guess deep down,

45:38.694 --> 45:42.164
I always knew
this day would come and--

45:45.076 --> 45:47.366
- May I come in, Ms. Tilly?

45:48.496 --> 45:50.326
- Be my guest.

45:50.373 --> 45:52.043
- Thank you.
- Mm-hmm.

45:52.083 --> 45:54.633
[bird chirps]

45:55.711 --> 45:57.051
[door slams]

45:57.088 --> 45:59.838
[crow caws]
[chuckles]

45:59.882 --> 46:04.802
To tell the truth,
I’m kind of relieved.

46:04.845 --> 46:07.715
Officer Gavin, have
you ever found yourself

46:07.765 --> 46:12.345
in a position where you have
to go against your own values

46:12.395 --> 46:16.065
and everything you believe
in as a human being

46:16.107 --> 46:19.817
and a Christian
to protect someone you love?

46:21.279 --> 46:22.649
- Yeah, actually--

46:22.697 --> 46:24.277
- Ha!

46:24.323 --> 46:27.033
- [grunts, gasps]

46:27.076 --> 46:29.996
- [laughs]

46:31.622 --> 46:33.422
Not me.

46:33.457 --> 46:36.077
Values are for losers.

46:36.127 --> 46:38.877
[laughing]

46:38.921 --> 46:41.471
[dramatic music]

46:41.507 --> 46:46.297
♪ ♪

46:46.345 --> 46:48.465
[keypad beeps]

46:48.514 --> 46:51.564
[call button buzzes]

46:51.600 --> 46:53.020
Shit.

46:53.060 --> 46:55.900
[The Slits’ "I Heard It
Through the Grapevine"]

46:55.938 --> 47:02.188
♪ ♪

47:03.779 --> 47:06.239
- ♪ I bet, I bet, I bet ♪

47:06.282 --> 47:09.372
♪ I bet you’re wondering
how I knew ♪

47:09.410 --> 47:12.960
♪ ’Bout your plans
to make me blue ♪

47:12.997 --> 47:16.577
♪ With some other guy
you knew before ♪

47:16.625 --> 47:20.295
♪ We’re two of a kind,
you know I love you more ♪

47:20.338 --> 47:24.008
♪ It took me by surprise
I must say ♪

47:24.050 --> 47:26.510
♪ When I found out yesterday ♪

47:26.552 --> 47:29.052
- [panting]

47:29.096 --> 47:31.346
- ♪ I heard it
through the grapevine ♪

47:31.390 --> 47:34.890
♪ Not much longer
will you be mine ♪

47:34.935 --> 47:37.345
- [timid chuckle]

47:37.396 --> 47:39.186
[sighs]

47:39.231 --> 47:42.281
Glen. Glenda.

47:42.318 --> 47:46.738
It’s so nice
to see your sweet faces.

47:46.781 --> 47:49.621
♪ ♪

47:49.658 --> 47:52.448
- ♪ I’m just about
to lose my mind ♪

47:52.495 --> 47:55.375
[playful spooky music]

47:55.414 --> 48:02.384
♪ ♪
